WEBVTT

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

01:02.062 --> 01:03.646
IN MOURNING
MO SEON-GYU

01:03.730 --> 01:09.152
JULY 2016

01:09.652 --> 01:11.571
<i>Back when all I had to give</i>

01:11.654 --> 01:13.823
<i>was my heart…</i>

01:18.787 --> 01:21.331
IM A-SOL, IM JI-SOL, KIM EUN-SU,
KIM A-RA, LEE CHAE-WON

01:22.999 --> 01:25.335
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

01:26.669 --> 01:29.047
<i>The desperate wish</i>

01:29.130 --> 01:31.007
<i>to convey how I felt any way I could.</i>

01:31.090 --> 01:32.842
Yeon Tae-seo!

01:33.343 --> 01:34.469
Here.

01:37.555 --> 01:39.265
<i>Did my feelings</i>

01:41.017 --> 01:42.393
<i>reach them properly?</i>

01:47.482 --> 01:54.447
STILL SHINING

01:56.574 --> 01:58.618
STAY YOUNGWON

02:47.542 --> 02:48.543
Where are you?

02:58.678 --> 03:00.138
<i>Get away from there, Tae-seo.</i>

03:05.226 --> 03:06.853
So where are you?

03:10.982 --> 03:13.359
Where is your exact location?

03:23.536 --> 03:25.038
That guy already left.

03:27.373 --> 03:28.875
He's gone, so stop worrying.

03:29.667 --> 03:30.835
Who says I'm worried?

03:32.462 --> 03:34.130
What are you doing here at this hour?

03:34.213 --> 03:36.341
What about you? Who's that girl?

03:36.424 --> 03:38.593
You came all the way
from Gangneung together,

03:38.676 --> 03:42.055
casually swapped drivers,
and then just went your separate ways.

03:42.138 --> 03:44.349
What kind of relationship is it
to be so casual?

03:50.188 --> 03:51.606
That's nice of her.

03:53.316 --> 03:55.902
You two must've talked a lot
on the way here.

03:57.195 --> 03:58.571
It really was nice of her,

03:58.655 --> 04:00.698
but don't offer
to buy her a meal to repay her.

04:04.911 --> 04:07.080
Did you end up meeting him?

04:08.081 --> 04:09.207
No.

04:10.458 --> 04:11.751
Did you see Park So-hyeon?

04:21.344 --> 04:23.054
She just turned up yesterday

04:23.137 --> 04:25.682
and said she'd take care of
my Tongyeong problem.

04:25.765 --> 04:27.475
But when I went to her room at dawn,

04:27.558 --> 04:30.687
I heard Seong-chan's voice
and rushed out in surprise.

04:30.770 --> 04:32.814
And in the middle of all that,

04:32.897 --> 04:35.066
I saw you get out of that woman's car

04:35.858 --> 04:38.152
and wondered who she was
and what's going on.

04:38.695 --> 04:39.988
That's all.

04:40.071 --> 04:43.366
I don't know what those two are up to.

04:45.159 --> 04:48.913
As long as you didn't run into him,
it's fine.

04:55.628 --> 04:57.588
Your expression says otherwise.

05:39.839 --> 05:43.176
The surgery was yesterday,
so it's been a day now, right?

05:44.135 --> 05:45.803
Tomorrow will be the second day.

05:46.637 --> 05:48.473
So she'll wake up tomorrow.

05:48.556 --> 05:50.266
It'll take two or three days.

05:53.644 --> 05:55.021
Grandpa, I'm here.

05:55.104 --> 05:56.522
I see. You came.

05:57.648 --> 05:59.734
By the way, I spoke to A-sol.

05:59.817 --> 06:02.695
I told her to get a meal out of you,
but she wants something else.

06:03.905 --> 06:04.864
Like what?

06:04.947 --> 06:06.324
I'm sure she'll tell you herself.

06:12.371 --> 06:13.706
You should eat before you go.

06:14.207 --> 06:15.917
I'll prepare the food.

06:18.544 --> 06:19.837
Do you know how?

06:20.922 --> 06:21.964
Yes.

06:27.261 --> 06:28.888
The house feels empty.

06:33.101 --> 06:37.146
YEON CHANG-SIK

06:45.863 --> 06:46.697
Grandpa.

06:46.781 --> 06:48.658
I think I'll have to make the rice again.

07:23.484 --> 07:24.735
CALLS

07:24.819 --> 07:25.653
EUN-A

07:25.736 --> 07:27.572
Visiting hours are open now.

07:48.926 --> 07:52.263
Let's shoot the inserts first.
Have the cameras set up in the yard.

07:52.346 --> 07:54.599
-And then, check the actors' blocking.
-Yes, sir.

07:54.682 --> 07:57.393
The restroom's at the end
of the hallway on the right.

08:00.855 --> 08:02.106
<i>Hello, sir.</i>

08:03.441 --> 08:05.234
Yes, they're here.

08:05.902 --> 08:08.696
They know this place better than I do.

08:08.779 --> 08:10.907
There's not much for me to help them with.

08:14.535 --> 08:17.788
Then I'll head out early today.

08:29.258 --> 08:31.594
<i>This is the revised contract. Take a look.</i>

08:32.094 --> 08:34.430
<i>You need to check everything,</i>
<i>so get down here now.</i>

08:34.514 --> 08:35.848
<i>Now we can finally rest easy.</i>

08:41.687 --> 08:44.565
Yeah, it's the second floor.
I'll be waiting outside.

08:44.649 --> 08:46.192
Okay, I'm almost there.

08:54.534 --> 08:55.535
This way.

08:58.204 --> 09:00.581
I mean, does this dead wood
produce oil or something?

09:00.665 --> 09:02.291
It just doesn't make any sense.

09:02.375 --> 09:07.088
I followed what I saw online.
I sanded it, oiled it, and did everything.

09:07.171 --> 09:09.382
It's been over a year,
but the oil's still coming out.

09:09.465 --> 09:10.883
It won't dry.

09:10.967 --> 09:13.135
It'll have to be sanded again.

09:15.012 --> 09:16.681
Is this desk being used?

09:18.224 --> 09:19.600
It's my dad's.

09:20.685 --> 09:22.103
What do I need to get ready?

09:22.979 --> 09:23.813
Nothing.

09:25.022 --> 09:26.065
Are you done checking?

09:26.857 --> 09:27.692
Yeah.

09:28.859 --> 09:30.361
Let's grab a bite downstairs.

09:30.444 --> 09:31.779
I haven't eaten yet today.

09:40.162 --> 09:42.748
Must be tough going back and forth
to the hospital while working.

09:42.832 --> 09:45.126
I used my vacation days
to free up time next week.

09:46.794 --> 09:48.254
When do you need it done by?

09:49.255 --> 09:52.633
He says he'll come back
to work next month,

09:53.134 --> 09:54.552
but it's always "next month."

09:54.635 --> 09:57.930
When I see him in March, he says April.
When it's November, he says December.

09:59.098 --> 10:01.559
He's with my mom
at my sister's house in Gapyeong.

10:01.642 --> 10:02.643
He has lung cancer.

10:04.395 --> 10:07.815
But he's holding up quite well.
I think he'll keep living there.

10:10.484 --> 10:12.653
I'm saying you can take your time.

10:13.154 --> 10:16.824
Seriously, taking your brother
to Gangneung wasn't any trouble at all.

10:16.907 --> 10:20.870
I quit my job working for a good company
in their tax department.

10:20.953 --> 10:24.123
Then, I took on my dad's work to help him,
only to get swamped.

10:25.207 --> 10:29.420
Now my dad says he's found a new life
and settled in Gapyeong with my mom.

10:29.503 --> 10:33.633
I'm the only one left at home,
and I was thinking, "What am I doing?"

10:35.843 --> 10:37.345
Then, I ended up seeing the ocean.

10:37.928 --> 10:40.431
It wasn't planned,
and it was only for a brief moment,

10:40.514 --> 10:42.808
but it still washed away months of stress.

10:43.893 --> 10:45.061
So I liked it.

10:54.612 --> 10:55.780
Hi, Eun-a.

10:57.615 --> 10:58.658
It's my girlfriend.

10:59.742 --> 11:00.743
What is it?

11:00.826 --> 11:02.995
<i>I figured you'd be back in Seoul by now.</i>

11:03.954 --> 11:04.789
<i>Right now, I…</i>

11:04.872 --> 11:06.832
Ma'am, can we have more kimchi?

11:06.916 --> 11:08.000
Sure.

11:08.084 --> 11:09.335
<i>It sounds like you're eating.</i>

11:10.002 --> 11:11.337
<i>Enjoy your lunch.</i>

11:11.420 --> 11:13.506
<i>-I'll call you back.</i>
-Okay.

11:18.677 --> 11:22.807
So… this keeps bothering me
every time I see you.

11:23.557 --> 11:25.518
It's about me giving you my name tag.

11:26.560 --> 11:29.647
There are different ways to interpret it.

11:29.730 --> 11:31.649
To say "I like you," I'd put in just mine.

11:31.732 --> 11:33.401
But there were several, right?

11:35.111 --> 11:36.904
I wanted to show you some support.

11:37.488 --> 11:39.698
My feelings at the time were

11:40.491 --> 11:43.452
sympathy 40%,

11:43.953 --> 11:45.287
respect 30%,

11:45.830 --> 11:47.498
and liking you around 30%.

11:48.082 --> 11:49.291
No, wait.

11:49.375 --> 11:51.127
It was 50, 30, and 20.

11:52.336 --> 11:53.629
Or was it 40, 40, and 20?

11:53.712 --> 11:54.547
Or 30?

11:54.630 --> 11:55.965
I must've looked really pitiful.

11:57.800 --> 11:58.801
Well, you don't now.

11:59.802 --> 12:02.388
I was really proud to see
how well you were doing.

12:03.722 --> 12:05.933
Remember the desk you used?
Seat One by the entrance?

12:06.475 --> 12:08.477
I used to sit there all the time too.

12:08.561 --> 12:10.938
It was easy to concentrate
when I sat there.

12:12.064 --> 12:14.984
I thought, "Someone endured far worse
and still made it through."

12:15.985 --> 12:18.112
You were my motivation.

12:18.195 --> 12:19.947
I wanted you to have a good life.

12:23.325 --> 12:25.619
Anyway, I'm just saying
that's what it was.

12:26.829 --> 12:30.499
It's just in case
you were wondering if I still liked you.

12:30.583 --> 12:32.543
It kept bothering me.

12:53.063 --> 12:54.982
<i>I had something</i>
<i>to take care of in Tongyeong,</i>

12:55.065 --> 12:57.276
<i>so I had to leave in a hurry.</i>

12:57.359 --> 12:59.778
<i>I'll come straight back</i>
<i>after checking some paperwork.</i>

12:59.862 --> 13:01.614
<i>It won't take even 30 minutes.</i>

13:01.697 --> 13:03.657
<i>I'll call you when I'm back in Seoul.</i>

13:16.295 --> 13:20.841
TONGYEONG BUS TERMINAL

13:32.937 --> 13:34.063
Show me.

13:34.563 --> 13:36.565
What's the rush? You can read it there.

13:48.827 --> 13:50.829
It's been revised
with the correct business type.

13:50.913 --> 13:52.289
The dates are the same.

13:52.373 --> 13:54.667
You can run it as planned
until March 20th.

13:56.335 --> 13:57.419
Just sign it.

14:02.591 --> 14:04.218
Are you…

14:05.010 --> 14:07.346
Are you angry right now?
It's all been settled.

14:08.013 --> 14:08.973
Just like that?

14:09.640 --> 14:10.891
How does this make sense?

14:10.975 --> 14:12.977
If it were this easy,
why did I spend months…

14:16.063 --> 14:18.315
How can Park So-hyeon appear
and make this all possible?

14:18.399 --> 14:19.441
LEASE AGREEMENT

14:19.525 --> 14:20.776
Why now?

14:25.197 --> 14:28.534
They apparently took in guests
while you were away in Seoul.

14:29.660 --> 14:31.996
All your stuff was still there,
so they're clearly crazy.

14:32.830 --> 14:35.749
They probably thought letting guests
sleep there was the end of it.

14:35.833 --> 14:38.669
They got complaints
and demands for refunds.

14:39.962 --> 14:42.548
They knew something was wrong,
and then Park So-hyeon turned up.

14:42.631 --> 14:44.383
You're the one who told her, right?

14:44.466 --> 14:46.260
What matters is that it's all settled now.

14:46.343 --> 14:49.555
And you told her
to ask Na-yeong where I was.

14:49.638 --> 14:51.599
Those scumbags backed down, okay?

14:51.682 --> 14:53.350
Who cares about Park So-hyeon right now?

15:09.366 --> 15:10.868
Let's not do this, okay?

15:10.951 --> 15:12.328
What's there to think about?

15:12.411 --> 15:14.204
That's your opinion, not mine.

15:14.288 --> 15:17.082
No wonder why Park So-hyeon
rushed over here in a panic.

15:17.166 --> 15:19.543
When I left this place,
I didn't leave the door open.

15:20.878 --> 15:23.756
Eun-a, I really don't understand you.

15:23.839 --> 15:25.049
What you…

15:27.801 --> 15:29.011
Give me a second.

15:34.808 --> 15:37.269
I thought you'd be excited
when this was all resolved.

15:39.146 --> 15:40.981
I thought you'd come running.

15:41.607 --> 15:42.942
Did I get Park So-hyeon involved?

15:43.025 --> 15:44.610
I did, but so what?

15:44.693 --> 15:46.487
We have to deal with it, don't we?

15:47.029 --> 15:48.614
Giving up is also an option.

15:48.697 --> 15:50.240
What kind of nonsense…

15:51.408 --> 15:53.911
Eun-a, you put so much
care and effort into that place.

15:53.994 --> 15:56.997
Now you can have it all back.
What exactly is the problem?

15:57.081 --> 15:58.582
Is this something to be mad about?

16:01.085 --> 16:02.628
There's nothing for you in Seoul.

16:02.711 --> 16:04.922
What's there to even think about?

16:06.340 --> 16:08.092
No matter how much care,

16:08.968 --> 16:10.302
effort, and love you put in,

16:13.263 --> 16:14.974
you can't hold onto it forever.

16:17.643 --> 16:19.019
Are you taking a jab at me?

16:24.274 --> 16:27.611
I'm not thinking the slightest bit
about getting back together with you.

16:27.695 --> 16:28.946
We're business partners.

16:31.657 --> 16:33.075
I won't say this again.

16:33.742 --> 16:36.495
If we sign the contract like this,
you won't get any compensation.

16:40.207 --> 16:43.127
Just check its condition.
Only you know what it was like before.

16:44.795 --> 16:46.755
Then, decide whether you want
bookings or not.

16:51.135 --> 16:52.428
Close the door.

17:23.917 --> 17:25.461
It's exactly the same.

17:25.544 --> 17:27.337
It's not like you were gone for that long.

17:33.010 --> 17:34.720
Even my keychain's still on.

17:36.555 --> 17:37.931
You go in first.

18:06.710 --> 18:09.129
That's not where the sofa goes.

18:13.342 --> 18:15.552
It's already become so shabby.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.072
All the handles are broken, and…

18:35.155 --> 18:36.532
Write it up and email it to me.

18:36.615 --> 18:39.243
Get in. I'll drop you off
at the bus terminal.

18:39.326 --> 18:40.994
No, I just need to hurry.

18:41.787 --> 18:42.746
I'm off.

18:43.455 --> 18:45.249
What's the rush?

18:45.332 --> 18:47.209
You don't even have
guests there from today.

18:48.085 --> 18:51.171
That place Park So-hyeon stayed at
isn't somewhere to work long-term.

18:52.214 --> 18:53.215
I'll handle it.

18:54.925 --> 18:56.677
You've barely even lived in Seoul.

18:56.760 --> 18:59.847
You never cared about it before,
so why are you suddenly so hung up on it?

18:59.930 --> 19:01.849
I didn't change my mind while I was there.

19:01.932 --> 19:03.934
I made up my mind here and left.

19:04.017 --> 19:05.352
I made the decision here.

19:05.435 --> 19:08.355
I had to drink with those scumbags
like nothing happened,

19:08.438 --> 19:09.606
and my mind was a mess too.

19:09.690 --> 19:11.984
I almost lost it a few times.

19:15.779 --> 19:18.740
But we're taking back what's ours.

19:18.824 --> 19:20.159
Why are you running away?

19:21.034 --> 19:24.663
You don't have to take bookings right now,
so just think it through

19:25.956 --> 19:26.790
and come back.

19:30.586 --> 19:32.754
Eun-a, I told you I'd drop you off.

19:34.131 --> 19:35.507
Geez, she's so stubborn.

19:51.982 --> 19:53.734
That's not possible.

20:06.622 --> 20:13.587
EUN-A
OKAY, HAVE A SAFE TRIP AND CALL ME LATER

20:26.141 --> 20:26.975
Hi, Hui-seo.

20:27.559 --> 20:28.602
Tae-seo.

20:29.311 --> 20:31.230
It's definitely two or three days, right?

20:31.313 --> 20:34.816
Today's the second day,
so she'll wake up tomorrow, right?

20:36.151 --> 20:37.236
<i>Right?</i>

20:39.404 --> 20:42.282
I'll be there tomorrow.

21:01.927 --> 21:04.221
You came home exhausted,
and your girlfriend's right here.

21:10.310 --> 21:12.145
Are you getting all emotional?

21:21.738 --> 21:22.781
You smell sweaty.

21:38.755 --> 21:40.924
-What's that?
-You haven't eaten yet, right?

21:41.591 --> 21:43.844
I got some sandwiches
in case you were hungry.

21:44.845 --> 21:45.846
Thanks.

21:51.476 --> 21:52.769
The sandwiches here are good.

21:53.937 --> 21:55.522
You're right. It's really soft.

21:55.605 --> 21:57.441
-You should eat too.
-Okay.

22:01.695 --> 22:03.864
It's nice to be eating together.

22:03.947 --> 22:04.990
I think so too.

22:16.626 --> 22:18.170
I had no idea,

22:18.253 --> 22:20.630
but Park So-hyeon knows
the person who blindsided me.

22:22.549 --> 22:24.426
I thought it was hopeless,

22:24.509 --> 22:26.845
but it was resolved,
and they sent over a contract.

22:26.928 --> 22:28.305
So I went over there to check it.

22:29.973 --> 22:32.225
What happens now if it's been resolved?

22:32.809 --> 22:34.394
Nothing's going to change.

22:34.478 --> 22:37.272
I'll keep working where I was working,
and I've found a place to live.

22:37.355 --> 22:39.066
I just need to move in on the set date.

22:40.192 --> 22:42.736
I can only run that place
for just a few more months anyway.

22:43.278 --> 22:44.738
Does that…

22:44.821 --> 22:46.073
Does that Seong-chan guy

22:47.074 --> 22:49.159
have something to do with your guesthouse?

22:54.122 --> 22:55.791
He introduced that spot to me.

22:56.917 --> 23:00.045
It turns out he only knew about it
through Park So-hyeon as well.

23:00.128 --> 23:03.340
We're partners,
but he's busy working at a hotel,

23:03.423 --> 23:05.008
so I basically ran it by myself.

23:05.509 --> 23:06.551
Does he live in Tongyeong?

23:07.302 --> 23:09.638
No, he lives in Geoje
at the hotel residence hall.

23:13.767 --> 23:15.352
You don't need to worry about him.

23:16.228 --> 23:18.063
I'm just worried for your safety.

23:18.939 --> 23:21.566
You don't usually see someone
being chased in a train station.

23:22.609 --> 23:23.860
I know, but…

23:24.569 --> 23:27.030
that guesthouse doesn't
automatically equal him.

23:27.739 --> 23:28.824
It's not like that.

23:30.283 --> 23:31.701
It might be mentioned now and then,

23:31.785 --> 23:33.745
but I can't have you
take it that way every time.

23:36.748 --> 23:38.625
It was originally an empty house.

23:40.377 --> 23:43.588
It was like I'd brought
a dying plant back to life.

23:44.548 --> 23:45.799
I felt proud,

23:46.383 --> 23:47.759
and it was fulfilling.

23:51.304 --> 23:52.639
So I have unexpected competition.

23:54.683 --> 23:57.060
I said a proper farewell
to your competition today.

24:06.903 --> 24:08.488
Have you…

24:10.532 --> 24:13.451
ever considered going back to Yeonwoo?

24:19.457 --> 24:20.375
I haven't.

24:21.501 --> 24:24.379
Yeonwoo was the first place I ruled out.

24:27.132 --> 24:27.966
What about you?

24:31.094 --> 24:32.095
I have to go.

24:33.430 --> 24:34.598
You'll be going close then.

24:37.517 --> 24:40.896
You said before that you want to keep
your distance because they're precious.

24:41.980 --> 24:44.941
My grandparents and Hui-seo
are precious to me,

24:45.525 --> 24:47.110
so I want to help them from a distance.

24:47.194 --> 24:49.154
When I'm too close, I burn out easily.

24:50.280 --> 24:52.949
<i>I didn't know what you meant at the time,</i>

24:53.533 --> 24:55.327
but that's what Yeonwoo is like to me.

24:57.913 --> 24:59.456
It's precious to me, but it hurts.

25:02.167 --> 25:04.794
Where will I end up after Tongyeong?

25:06.087 --> 25:07.631
What do you think?

25:11.760 --> 25:14.888
If you're asking for my opinion
about your future,

25:14.971 --> 25:16.348
can I…

25:16.431 --> 25:19.142
take it that I'm a part of it?

25:20.769 --> 25:22.145
Instead of just your future,

25:23.271 --> 25:25.690
I'll take it as our future.

25:26.733 --> 25:28.151
And that's what I'll think about.

25:31.404 --> 25:32.489
Can I do that?

25:38.662 --> 25:41.081
Is factoring me in

25:42.040 --> 25:43.083
going to help?

25:44.376 --> 25:46.586
You already have a lot on your mind,

25:46.670 --> 25:48.964
but will that really help?

25:49.047 --> 25:49.881
Yeah.

25:56.137 --> 25:57.222
That's nice.

25:58.515 --> 26:00.267
Now I have something I can do for you.

26:03.186 --> 26:04.312
Let's do that then.

26:08.108 --> 26:09.526
Let's give it some thought.

26:29.796 --> 26:31.214
Thank you. Have a nice trip.

26:39.973 --> 26:41.766
Sorry, I just need to take this call.

26:41.850 --> 26:42.851
Sure.

26:46.271 --> 26:47.272
Hello?

26:48.398 --> 26:49.816
Yes, how have you been?

27:03.872 --> 27:07.042
<i>Ga-on's family canceled before,</i>
<i>but they're coming as planned.</i>

27:07.125 --> 27:10.211
<i>If you don't have time,</i>
<i>I'll make it work just for them,</i>

27:10.295 --> 27:11.588
<i>so send me your manual.</i>

27:18.178 --> 27:21.556
BYEONNWI OPERATIONS MANUAL

27:23.641 --> 27:25.769
ROOM AMENITIES

27:43.119 --> 27:44.412
<i>It's simple.</i>

27:44.496 --> 27:47.374
<i>I'll do what needs to be done,</i>
<i>ask him to help out, and then come back.</i>

27:48.500 --> 27:50.835
<i>I don't need to make Tae-seo worry.</i>

27:50.919 --> 27:52.170
<i>I can handle this myself.</i>

28:25.995 --> 28:29.290
MO SEON-GYU

29:09.914 --> 29:11.040
Who's there?

29:29.058 --> 29:30.310
<i>The cleaning's done.</i>

29:30.894 --> 29:32.896
I also sent you the manual just in case.

29:33.855 --> 29:34.689
Don't do breakfast.

29:35.273 --> 29:37.066
They'll understand
if you explain it to them.

29:38.610 --> 29:40.653
Tell me about breakfast.
I'll give it a go.

29:42.655 --> 29:44.073
You can't do it.

29:46.367 --> 29:49.537
I just steam some vegetables,
blend some juice, and toast some bread.

29:49.621 --> 29:50.789
That's all, isn't it?

29:53.249 --> 29:55.210
We have to do it for Ga-on's family.

29:57.962 --> 29:58.797
The steamer is…

29:59.464 --> 30:00.465
I'll get it out for you.

30:01.591 --> 30:03.343
Hey, where's that thing?

30:03.426 --> 30:04.844
That tiny little serving table?

30:04.928 --> 30:06.346
I'll give you that as well.

30:08.389 --> 30:11.476
Then I better wash the cauldron.

30:13.311 --> 30:14.479
I used to do it all the time.

30:15.396 --> 30:16.731
And that.

30:19.150 --> 30:19.984
What is it?

30:20.068 --> 30:21.611
Your stuff from the kitchen.

30:22.320 --> 30:25.448
I haven't cleaned the room yet.
You do it and take your things.

30:25.532 --> 30:27.951
-Are you coming back?
-I'm saying you should take your stuff.

30:31.120 --> 30:33.498
Why bother moving my stuff
if you're not even coming back?

30:33.581 --> 30:35.333
I'm already busy juggling two jobs.

30:36.543 --> 30:40.213
You can move my stuff out for good
when you're sure about coming back.

30:41.214 --> 30:44.717
I don't even have much stuff here.
Maybe some clothes from our three months.

31:25.550 --> 31:26.634
Seong-chan.

31:28.845 --> 31:30.513
Can you manage things here?

31:32.390 --> 31:34.601
I said I'd handle Ga-on's booking.

31:35.184 --> 31:37.145
You need time anyway

31:37.812 --> 31:39.606
to wrap things up in Seoul.

31:45.570 --> 31:46.571
Wait, from now on?

31:49.240 --> 31:50.742
Rather than leave it empty,

31:51.951 --> 31:54.037
take at least one booking a month.

31:54.120 --> 31:56.289
Take more if you can handle it.

31:56.372 --> 31:58.625
You know which guests come every season.

31:59.334 --> 32:00.919
Just do it until the lease is up.

32:03.588 --> 32:04.964
I want you to run it.

32:11.304 --> 32:13.014
You tell me to move out my stuff

32:13.097 --> 32:15.141
but want me to take bookings.

32:16.100 --> 32:18.102
Figure out what you want to do first.

32:20.730 --> 32:22.899
You're going back to the hotel, right?

32:24.484 --> 32:26.152
I'll get off here.

32:32.492 --> 32:37.455
TONGYEONG BUS TERMINAL

34:46.501 --> 34:49.045
Look at us. What are we even doing?

34:58.638 --> 35:00.348
Grandpa, let me do that.

35:03.684 --> 35:05.103
Go sleep at home.

35:05.686 --> 35:08.564
-Stop that. Give it here.
-Never.

35:13.402 --> 35:16.114
We need to be smart about this.

35:17.240 --> 35:20.076
When Grandma wakes up,
that's when the real trouble starts.

35:20.159 --> 35:23.788
She'll wake up
before I can leave the hospital.

35:23.871 --> 35:25.998
-We need a rotation.
-I can take time off too.

35:26.082 --> 35:27.792
No way. It'll just complicate things.

35:27.875 --> 35:29.293
Your schedule's all over the place.

35:30.294 --> 35:31.796
Hyang-gi worked something out.

35:32.630 --> 35:35.675
But you and I have to take turns
to come every day, Grandpa.

35:35.758 --> 35:37.301
It's going to test our endurance.

35:37.385 --> 35:39.804
So right now,
while Grandma's still in the hospital,

35:39.887 --> 35:41.681
you should rest at home, Grandpa.

35:43.182 --> 35:44.475
And Tae-seo,

35:44.559 --> 35:46.769
make sure you keep talking to Grandma.

35:46.853 --> 35:49.480
Just staring at her
won't help her wake up.

35:50.439 --> 35:54.485
I washed this just now
in the bathroom with hot water.

35:56.904 --> 35:58.573
Grandma can't stand anything dirty.

35:58.656 --> 36:01.492
She'll hate it
if she sees dirt under her nails.

36:07.623 --> 36:10.459
THE DIFFERENT APPEALS
OF DRIVING SUBWAYS AND TRAINS

36:10.543 --> 36:13.504
I FIRST CONSIDERED CHANGING JOBS
BECAUSE OF THE ROUTES

36:19.302 --> 36:21.345
Visitors can come in now.

36:21.429 --> 36:22.805
Okay.

36:35.568 --> 36:36.611
Grandma.

36:40.281 --> 36:41.699
I…

36:47.580 --> 36:48.581
So…

36:53.961 --> 36:55.588
My expiration date…

36:59.675 --> 37:02.011
I think I can decide on my own
when that will be.

37:17.985 --> 37:19.528
Hae-jin, it's me.

37:20.279 --> 37:22.365
Can you cover for me just for today?

37:22.448 --> 37:24.450
<i>I just need to handle</i>
<i>the front desk, right?</i>

37:25.451 --> 37:27.954
<i>You owe me a big, fancy dinner.</i>

38:12.331 --> 38:13.708
All set.

38:20.172 --> 38:21.632
AN OPEN SPACE SURROUNDED BY NATURE

38:21.716 --> 38:24.176
A PLACE TO REST BENEATH SUNLIGHT
FILTERING THROUGH THE TREES

38:53.164 --> 38:54.457
Goodbye.

38:57.376 --> 39:00.463
MO SEON-GYU

39:00.546 --> 39:01.756
<i>Dad.</i>

39:01.839 --> 39:06.719
<i>I dreamed, built,</i>
<i>and accomplished a lot in this place.</i>

39:07.845 --> 39:09.305
<i>You saw all that, right?</i>

39:10.723 --> 39:11.974
<i>Then that's all I need.</i>

39:13.392 --> 39:15.353
TAEYONG EXPRESS

39:15.436 --> 39:16.896
TONGYEONG BUS TERMINAL

40:31.762 --> 40:33.973
There's a lost item in Car 2-4.

40:48.404 --> 40:49.738
What are you doing here?

40:52.491 --> 40:54.368
I missed you too much.

40:57.163 --> 40:58.497
Did something happen?

41:18.267 --> 41:20.603
We can see each other when we want to.

41:24.607 --> 41:26.400
That counts as something for us.

41:33.324 --> 41:34.533
Tae-seo.

41:38.829 --> 41:40.414
This is the right place.

41:44.460 --> 41:46.253
This place is what's real.

42:11.862 --> 42:14.198
What is she, a helpful elf or something?
How foolish.

42:27.628 --> 42:29.338
She's seriously not coming back?

42:29.421 --> 42:32.383
The left side looks a little off.
Let's adjust it a tiny bit.

42:32.466 --> 42:34.009
Yes, right away.

42:34.093 --> 42:35.636
We have to clear the back area anyway.

42:35.719 --> 42:36.720
Let's do it later.

42:37.721 --> 42:39.723
Jeong-min, please help out with this.

42:47.356 --> 42:48.899
Clean up over there.

42:48.983 --> 42:49.984
Got it.

42:50.943 --> 42:52.361
Can you try calling the actor?

42:52.444 --> 42:54.154
Where's the props department?

42:56.782 --> 42:57.616
So…

42:59.034 --> 43:00.035
basically,

43:00.953 --> 43:03.622
I originally had a job lined up.

43:03.706 --> 43:05.833
It was a place run by someone I know,

43:05.916 --> 43:08.877
but it looks like
they won't be able to open this year.

43:09.378 --> 43:11.547
They acted like
they were going to open any day now.

43:12.881 --> 43:14.508
I can't believe it either.

43:16.677 --> 43:17.886
You mean…

43:18.554 --> 43:19.638
Just for this month.

43:19.722 --> 43:21.223
I need to look for a place too.

43:21.307 --> 43:23.934
Try to hold out somehow
just until the end of this month.

43:24.018 --> 43:25.352
Okay?

43:25.436 --> 43:27.104
I'll get it sorted out by then.

43:27.688 --> 43:29.481
Want help finding
a temporary place to stay?

43:33.027 --> 43:34.445
Anyway,

43:34.528 --> 43:36.572
it's not really for me to say,

43:36.655 --> 43:38.949
and I thought it'd be better
to find my replacement soon

43:39.033 --> 43:40.618
so I didn't say anything.

43:40.701 --> 43:43.245
But the owner here has no interest
in running a guesthouse.

43:43.829 --> 43:45.831
After this shoot,
they'll have another pop-up here.

43:45.914 --> 43:47.916
You're only here
to open and close the doors.

43:48.709 --> 43:50.836
I need to do at least that.

43:53.297 --> 43:55.883
I promise you,
this place will be closing soon.

43:56.467 --> 43:58.427
You should start
looking for a hotel job now.

43:59.386 --> 44:02.056
A place to stay and a job…

44:02.765 --> 44:04.391
I need to find everything again.

44:05.643 --> 44:06.477
Well…

44:07.144 --> 44:08.437
I mean…

44:08.520 --> 44:11.273
That's one way to look at it.

44:12.983 --> 44:14.485
I'm sorry.

44:29.875 --> 44:32.711
<i>If you're sure,</i>
<i>we should close this place.</i>

44:33.587 --> 44:36.173
<i>I can contact Ga-on's family.</i>

44:36.256 --> 44:38.300
<i>And I'll clear this place out myself.</i>

44:39.635 --> 44:40.886
<i>Clear out…</i>

45:59.506 --> 46:00.674
Now I'm feeling awake.

46:24.531 --> 46:26.909
KTC RAILWAY LAWS AND REGULATIONS

46:44.635 --> 46:47.095
Including blood pressure,
her vitals are stable.

46:47.179 --> 46:49.181
Her intracranial pressure
is stabilizing too.

46:49.932 --> 46:51.433
If she's still stable in the morning,

46:51.517 --> 46:53.977
we can move her into a regular room
within the next two days.

47:15.958 --> 47:21.213
MART

47:24.091 --> 47:26.552
Goodness, you came all the way from Seoul.
What happened?

47:26.635 --> 47:28.971
My wife is getting better.

47:29.054 --> 47:31.390
Goodness, what a relief.

47:32.140 --> 47:32.975
That's great.

47:33.058 --> 47:34.393
It is.

47:35.227 --> 47:37.062
-I'll grab a bottle of soju.
-Sure.

48:05.048 --> 48:06.049
Let's go.

48:07.884 --> 48:09.970
Here, this is some kimchi stew.

48:10.554 --> 48:11.930
Heat it for him.

48:12.014 --> 48:13.140
Do you have rice?

48:13.223 --> 48:15.767
Leave it. We have rice.

48:15.851 --> 48:17.102
-Go on now.
-Thank you.

48:17.185 --> 48:18.353
Sure. Get going.

48:18.437 --> 48:19.771
-Bye.
-Take care.

48:34.620 --> 48:37.789
Did you ever have a drink with your dad?

48:38.707 --> 48:39.791
No.

48:48.884 --> 48:50.594
Just have one glass.

49:03.106 --> 49:06.026
I'm glad I'm at least still here
to pour you a drink.

49:17.162 --> 49:17.996
Grandpa.

49:18.747 --> 49:22.042
Did you know
I wanted to drive trains as a child?

49:23.251 --> 49:24.961
I wanted to drive the Sea Train,

49:25.045 --> 49:26.588
because when I was little, I saw Mom…

49:27.422 --> 49:28.965
working there.

49:30.342 --> 49:33.637
Once I pass the tests and interview,
I can choose my region.

49:34.513 --> 49:35.514
I'm thinking Gangneung

49:35.597 --> 49:37.557
or somewhere along the east coast.

49:37.641 --> 49:38.975
Leave it all to Hui-seo.

49:40.018 --> 49:41.978
He'll be out of the hospital soon.

49:42.062 --> 49:44.564
He said he'd look after your grandma
in the hospital

49:44.648 --> 49:46.733
until the day she's discharged.

49:47.359 --> 49:49.611
That's his motivation to get better,

49:49.695 --> 49:51.488
so just let him do it.

49:52.364 --> 49:53.615
Hui-seo…

49:54.950 --> 49:59.037
needs to help someone
to become confident and healthier.

50:00.539 --> 50:02.624
Just hang on for a few more days,

50:02.708 --> 50:07.003
and before you know it,
everything will go back to the way it was.

50:07.838 --> 50:10.382
You won't even remember it
once this is all over.

50:16.096 --> 50:18.140
Don't forget to see Jin-su.

50:18.223 --> 50:19.933
He's been worried sick.

50:25.480 --> 50:26.523
<i>Don't you dare come here.</i>

50:26.606 --> 50:28.525
<i>I can even go to the bathroom on my own.</i>

50:28.608 --> 50:31.695
<i>I've got amazing recovery skills.</i>

50:31.778 --> 50:32.612
I'll admit that.

50:33.655 --> 50:35.240
<i>-Get some rest.</i>
-Okay, bye.

50:54.384 --> 50:56.428
Yeonwoo's been ruled out.

50:58.555 --> 51:00.974
Seoul or…

51:02.768 --> 51:04.019
Tongyeong

51:04.770 --> 51:05.604
and the east coast.

51:08.023 --> 51:09.649
EUN-A

51:21.536 --> 51:22.788
STAY BYEONNWI

51:24.539 --> 51:25.707
"Byeonnwi"?

51:32.380 --> 51:33.381
STAY BYEONNWI

51:47.354 --> 51:50.315
FOR RESERVATIONS AND INQUIRIES,
CLICK THE LINK BELOW

51:56.947 --> 51:58.365
REPOSTED

52:26.017 --> 52:28.019
-Hey, you came.
-Hi.

52:29.563 --> 52:31.398
So about Hui-seo…

52:32.399 --> 52:34.609
I'm never taking Hui-seo anywhere again.

52:34.693 --> 52:36.695
He was tense the whole way there.

52:36.778 --> 52:39.239
I still get chills thinking about it.

52:39.322 --> 52:41.783
Anyway, I'm really sorry.

52:43.743 --> 52:46.955
No, Hui-seo finally worked up the courage,
and you helped him.

52:50.500 --> 52:52.836
Hey, on my way home,

52:52.919 --> 52:54.337
I saw the last house lit up.

52:55.463 --> 52:56.798
It's been dark until now.

53:30.749 --> 53:31.666
Who are…

53:34.461 --> 53:35.629
You…

53:35.712 --> 53:37.130
It's you, right?

53:45.221 --> 53:46.264
There.

53:49.267 --> 53:52.020
I should stop telling Eun-a
to come live here.

53:52.103 --> 53:53.521
There's a lot that needs work.

53:54.189 --> 53:55.649
It's been left empty for too long.

53:57.108 --> 53:58.944
Eun-a shouldn't come back here.

53:59.027 --> 54:00.362
It's in good condition.

54:00.445 --> 54:02.113
It just needs a bit of cleaning.

54:02.697 --> 54:04.783
It'd take at least a month
to clean this place.

54:05.784 --> 54:08.286
I even bought these instant coffee sticks

54:08.370 --> 54:10.830
so I can make some
for elderly folks passing by.

54:11.414 --> 54:12.624
But nobody passed by.

54:13.291 --> 54:15.794
Then again,
they wouldn't have come inside anyway.

54:20.590 --> 54:21.675
In Tongyeong,

54:23.134 --> 54:25.053
there's a guesthouse Eun-a used to run.

54:25.762 --> 54:27.597
I'd only ever heard about it,

54:27.681 --> 54:29.975
but when I finally went there
a few days ago…

54:34.062 --> 54:35.480
Goodness.

54:36.356 --> 54:38.274
It reminded me of this house

54:38.358 --> 54:41.027
even though she didn't take
even a spoon from this place.

54:41.903 --> 54:43.822
It made me think of Seon-gyu.

54:46.324 --> 54:50.745
It was precious to her,
but those scumbags put her through a lot.

54:54.082 --> 54:55.792
You haven't seen her in a while, right?

54:58.003 --> 54:59.170
You two were unbelievable.

55:00.964 --> 55:02.340
So was I.

55:02.424 --> 55:04.259
Why did I think I could lecture you?

55:10.765 --> 55:11.599
This is the address.

55:11.683 --> 55:13.268
The one next door is her house.

55:13.351 --> 55:15.061
But it's basically the same place.

55:15.145 --> 55:16.938
She receives packages at this one.

55:17.022 --> 55:19.607
The guesthouse is called Byeonnwi.

55:20.191 --> 55:21.401
It's so hard to pronounce.

55:21.484 --> 55:22.318
"Byeonnwi."

55:23.028 --> 55:27.490
Apparently, it means
"sunlight filtering through small gaps."

55:27.574 --> 55:30.910
Like the light that comes in
at an angle into the shade.

55:31.870 --> 55:33.246
That one ray of light.

55:33.329 --> 55:38.001
It's like how cats find spots like that
and curl up there even in the dark.

55:38.877 --> 55:40.253
It's warm.

55:41.212 --> 55:42.589
That's what that place is like.

55:44.007 --> 55:45.425
Eun-a found her way there.

55:47.302 --> 55:49.929
You should visit.
Once it's behind you, you can be friends.

55:51.139 --> 55:51.973
She'll be glad.

56:01.024 --> 56:02.317
EUN-A'S GUESTHOUSE

56:07.280 --> 56:10.158
Seon-gyu used to pick flowers
every morning.

56:10.241 --> 56:13.620
He'd stick them in random cups
and leave them around the house.

56:15.330 --> 56:16.664
Eun-a does exactly the same.

56:23.338 --> 56:25.381
Gosh, where is my head?

56:25.465 --> 56:28.551
Hey, don't keep standing there.
Grab a chair and sit down.

56:29.135 --> 56:31.221
-Do you want a drink?
-No, I'm fine.

56:32.180 --> 56:33.431
Right, okay.

56:35.767 --> 56:37.143
I'm getting carried away.

56:37.852 --> 56:39.604
How's Hui-seo? Is he well?

56:40.355 --> 56:41.189
I'm going to go.

56:45.360 --> 56:47.153
Why are you acting like I have the plague?

56:49.239 --> 56:51.449
Everyone here hates me.

56:52.200 --> 56:54.994
All because I should've stayed
right by Seon-gyu's side,

56:55.745 --> 56:57.372
but I was gone for a moment.

57:00.708 --> 57:01.709
Take care.

57:01.793 --> 57:03.294
You've grown up nicely.

57:04.796 --> 57:06.214
I'll lock the gate.

57:33.575 --> 57:35.410
It wasn't for a moment.

57:35.493 --> 57:36.870
You went to Hawaii.

57:36.953 --> 57:40.290
Even though you knew
you weren't supposed to leave him alone.

57:43.710 --> 57:44.794
I went home.

57:45.378 --> 57:47.172
Hawaii is my home. Didn't you know that?

57:47.255 --> 57:49.174
I went back for the first time in years.

57:50.550 --> 57:51.926
I checked 500 times.

57:52.010 --> 57:53.386
He was completely fine.

57:53.470 --> 57:56.055
Depression? Not even a hint of it.

57:56.806 --> 57:59.434
He was completely fine
even without taking his medicine.

58:00.018 --> 58:01.311
I never even imagined it.

58:15.658 --> 58:17.202
I had my own selfish reasons too.

58:19.454 --> 58:23.249
When I heard that Eun-a and my mom
were having a great time,

58:24.459 --> 58:26.294
I wanted to be there too.

58:27.629 --> 58:30.215
In that corridor over there,
there's a photo of Eun-a.

58:31.466 --> 58:34.552
My mom actually sent me pictures of her

58:35.637 --> 58:37.347
even though my mom
hardly ever contacts me.

58:37.430 --> 58:39.224
She must've adored Eun-a that much.

58:41.392 --> 58:44.270
I had it printed and put it there.

58:44.354 --> 58:47.565
Whenever Seon-gyu saw that photo,

58:48.233 --> 58:49.067
he would smile.

58:51.194 --> 58:53.071
I left, believing in that photo.

58:55.490 --> 58:56.908
Honestly…

58:57.492 --> 58:59.869
After breaking up with you in December,

58:59.953 --> 59:02.539
Eun-a went to intern in Hawaii.

59:03.540 --> 59:05.917
She kept wavering about going
and then finally did.

59:07.669 --> 59:09.087
We broke up in December?

59:09.671 --> 59:12.215
Around December. It was then.

59:13.299 --> 59:15.260
Still, just in case,

59:15.343 --> 59:18.137
I asked Seong-chan
to look in on him every day,

59:18.221 --> 59:20.139
without fail.

59:25.186 --> 59:27.313
That Seong-chan person.

59:27.397 --> 59:28.898
Was he really that trustworthy?

59:30.483 --> 59:32.110
I had known him for a long time.

59:32.193 --> 59:33.278
I see.

59:35.196 --> 59:36.781
Did you hear how Eun-a was doing

59:36.864 --> 59:39.826
through this Seong-chan person?

59:40.493 --> 59:41.661
More or less.

59:47.292 --> 59:49.711
Eun-a must have kept him close

59:50.461 --> 59:53.756
because he was updating you
on how she was doing.

59:54.340 --> 59:58.052
It sounds like she thought
she would do at least that much for you.

59:58.136 --> 01:00:01.556
That's something Eun-a would do.

01:00:02.056 --> 01:00:04.434
Her? I'm not so sure.

01:00:05.101 --> 01:00:07.061
You haven't seen her at all, right?

01:00:08.229 --> 01:00:09.063
Look.

01:00:09.647 --> 01:00:11.524
This is last year.

01:00:13.568 --> 01:00:15.278
This is her guesthouse.

01:00:15.361 --> 01:00:17.280
I was sent this as soon as it opened.

01:00:18.781 --> 01:00:21.200
This is from three years ago.

01:00:23.369 --> 01:00:24.495
This is 2020.

01:00:25.330 --> 01:00:26.164
This is 2019.

01:00:30.335 --> 01:00:31.711
Seong-chan sent them to me.

01:00:31.794 --> 01:00:34.464
He knew that I missed her.

01:00:35.673 --> 01:00:37.592
These were all…

01:00:37.675 --> 01:00:40.011
-taken by that Seong-chan person?
-Yes.

01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:42.889
They dated for a brief while
and then broke up.

01:00:44.223 --> 01:00:45.850
They're not a good match.

01:00:45.933 --> 01:00:48.519
He isolates her from everyone.

01:00:48.603 --> 01:00:50.730
But Eun-a loves being around people.

01:01:02.450 --> 01:01:04.994
<i>That guy from the station,</i>
<i>her business partner,</i>

01:01:05.870 --> 01:01:07.705
<i>her link with Park So-hyeon,</i>

01:01:07.789 --> 01:01:10.041
<i>and the person she dated for three months</i>

01:01:10.541 --> 01:01:11.959
<i>were all the same person.</i>

01:01:14.128 --> 01:01:15.880
<i>In the past decade of Eun-a's life…</i>

01:01:18.174 --> 01:01:20.009
<i>he was the only one present.</i>

01:01:48.454 --> 01:01:49.622
Rule Tongyeong out as well.

01:02:07.098 --> 01:02:08.224
Don't go there.

01:02:29.036 --> 01:02:32.540
STILL SHINING

01:03:01.402 --> 01:03:03.404
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
